<br>
No.  It's a limitation in the client.  A long time ago the guy in charge of client coding hinted that he would be altering the interface to do away with the 640x480 screen (a more AO-like interface), but apparently that hasn't been a high priority.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't suggest you turn the "same screen size" option off, because then your monitor will have to resync to 640x480 (and back to whatever resolution you use) every time you need to loot or look at your spellbook.  This will not only cause an annoying delay and "clicK" from the monitor, but it could greatly shorten your monitor's life. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urobart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.iconarchive.com/icon/cartoon/looney_by_iconfactory/SpeedyGonzales.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/01 11:14:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1134.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Video Mode question</span><hr size=1> I've done the monitor switching modes thing.  Very annoying.  I 'm glad that they at least changed tracking so it doesn't switch modes when we hit it.  I wouldn't use higher res mode when that was the case.<br>
